      "amount": "½ tsp",
      "notes": "freshly ground"
    },
    {
      "name": "Lime",
      "amount": "1",
      "notes": "zest and juice"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in the minced garlic and grated ginger, cooking until fragrant, about 1 minute.",
    "Add the toor dal and cherry tomatoes, and cook for another 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in the vegetable broth and coconut milk, then bring to a simmer.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper, and reduce heat to low.",
    "Cover the pot and let the stew slow-cook for 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add the chopped mint leaves and lime zest in the last 5 minutes of cooking.",
    "Squeeze in the lime juice and stir to combine.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with extra mint if desired."
  ],
